data.enText: a former male student of a school, college or university

ex.chText: 我父亲毕业于佛罗里达大学。
ex.enText: My father is an alumnus of UF.
My mother is a Cambridge alumna.

ex.chText: 我的父母毕业于同一所学校。
ex.enText: My parents are alumni of the same school.

synonyms.bx: 源自拉丁语，本义为“学童，小学生”，现尤指中学或大学的男毕业生。在美国英语中，alumni ( alumnus 的复数) 指男／女毕业生，alumna (复数为 alumnae ) 指女毕业生。

ex.chText: 她是美国文学专业的毕业生。
ex.enText: She is a graduate in American Literature.

ex.chText: 我侄女是个高中毕业生。
ex.enText: My niece is a high-school graduate.

synonyms.bx: 尤指完成学士学位课程的大学毕业生，也可泛指大学、中学等的毕业生。

tr: a person who has received a degree from a school (high school or college or university)

value.def: The alumni of a school, college, or university are the people who used to be students there.
